org.json.stream

Class JSONLexer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.json.stream.JSONLexer

  • public final class JSONLexer
extends java.lang.Object
    A JSONLexer takes a source stream and extracts characters and tokens from it. It does not perform any sanity checks on the order that tokens appear. It is used by JSONStreamReader class to tokenise JSON source streams.

      • nextString

        public <T extends java.lang.Appendable> T nextString(T sb,
                                                     long maxLen)
                                              throws JSONException
        Return the characters up to the next close quote character. Backslash escape sequences are processed. The formal JSON format only allows string values within double quotes.

        Most practical parsers will limit the length of a string to one expressible by a String object, or writable to a File.

        Type Parameters:
        T - a subtype of Appendable, returned to the caller for chaining purposes
        Parameters:
        sb - the Appendable to which the String value is appended
        maxLen - the maximum length of the decoded string value, <= 0 to limit to Long.MAX_VALUE
        Returns:
        the supplied Appendable object
        Throws:
        JSONException - Unterminated string.

      • nextNumber

        public boolean nextNumber(java.lang.Appendable sb,
                          int mDigits,
                          int eDigits)
                   throws JSONException
        Parse a number strictly according to the JSON specification.

        Most practical JSON parsers limit the number values to those expressible by Long or Double values.

        Parameters:
        sb - The Appendable to which the parsed character sequence is appended
        mDigits - maximum number of mantissa digits to be parsed, <= 0 to limit to Integer.MAX_VALUE
        eDigits - maximum number of exponent digits to be parsed, 0 for no exponent, or < 0 to limit to Integer.MAX_VALUE
        Returns:
        true if the number is a floating point value, otherwise false to indicate an integer value
        Throws:
        JSONException
